        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2012-10-30 14:53:29.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nAdding more positional parameters makes parsing the options more complex, and also makes using this function more complex.\n\nIt would be better to allow the user to specify a FID directly instead of just of the objid for FID-on-OST:\n\n lctl destroy [0x240000003:0x44:0x0]\n\nor with IDIF FIDs:\n\n lctl destroy [0x100010000:0x1234:0x0]\n\nIt would be easy to detect this case by checking for a FID format first, then fall back to a plain objid if no FID is found.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
